geneVariantDescriptions.description: JAZF1-SUZ12 results from the fusion of JAZF1 and SUZ12, which leads to increased cell proliferation, results in impaired Polycomb repressive complex 2 formation and decreased histone methyltransferase activity in one study (PMID: 27845897), but restores Ezh2 protein level and H3K27 trimethylation in SUZ12-deficient cells and promotes survival in another study (PMID: 18077430), and therefore, the effect on protein function is unknown. JAZF1-SUZ12 fusion is associated with endometrial stromal cell tumors (PMID: 11371647, PMID: 26879382).

references.title: JAZF1/SUZ12 gene fusion in endometrial stromal sarcomas.
The JAZF1-SUZ12 fusion protein disrupts PRC2 complexes and impairs chromatin repression during human endometrial stromal tumorogenesis.
Frequent fusion of the JAZF1 and JJAZ1 genes in endometrial stromal tumors.
Effects of rearrangement and allelic exclusion of JJAZ1/SUZ12 on cell proliferation and survival.
